{
  "page": "Lord Bracken (father of Otho)",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Bracken\" title=\"House Bracken\"><img alt=\"House Bracken.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e5/House_Bracken.svg/50px-House_Bracken.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e5/House_Bracken.svg/75px-House_Bracken.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/e5/House_Bracken.svg/100px-House_Bracken.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Lord Bracken</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Bracken\" title=\"House Bracken\"><img alt=\"House Bracken.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e5/House_Bracken.svg/50px-House_Bracken.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e5/House_Bracken.svg/75px-House_Bracken.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/e5/House_Bracken.svg/100px-House_Bracken.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_the_Stone_Hedge\" title=\"Lord of the Stone Hedge\">Lord of the Stone Hedge</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Bracken\" title=\"House Bracken\">House Bracken</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Rivermen\" title=\"Rivermen\">Rivermen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/211_AC\" title=\"211 AC\">211&#160;AC</a> or <a href=\"/index.php/212_AC\" title=\"212 AC\">212&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><br />the <a href=\"/index.php/Trident\" title=\"Trident\">Trident</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> <small>(unconfirmed)</small></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li>Son<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Otho_Bracken\" title=\"Otho Bracken\">Otho Bracken</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Sworn_Sword\" title=\"The Sworn Sword\">The Sworn Sword</a></i> (mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Lord Bracken</b> was the Lord of the <a href=\"/index.php/Stone_Hedge\" title=\"Stone Hedge\">Stone Hedge</a> and the head of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Bracken\" title=\"House Bracken\">House Bracken</a> during the reign of kings <a href=\"/index.php/Daeron_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Daeron II Targaryen\">Daeron II</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Aerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerys I Targaryen\">Aerys I Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> His given name is unknown.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Bracken_(father_of_Otho)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Blackfyre_Rebellion\" title=\"First Blackfyre Rebellion\">First Blackfyre Rebellion</a>, a Lord Bracken (presumably, the father of Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Otho_Bracken\" title=\"Otho Bracken\">Otho</a>) declared for <a href=\"/index.php/House_Blackfyre\" title=\"House Blackfyre\">House Blackfyre</a>. He sailed to <a href=\"/index.php/Myr\" title=\"Myr\">Myr</a> to hire crossbowmen to aid <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_I_Blackfyre\" title=\"Daemon I Blackfyre\">Daemon I Blackfyre</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Bittersteel\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bittersteel\">Bittersteel</a>, but was delayed by storms.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/211_AC\" title=\"211 AC\">211&#160;AC</a>, Lord Bracken is dying. As he outlived his eldest son, who died during the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Spring_Sickness\" title=\"Great Spring Sickness\">Great Spring Sickness</a>, his second son, the belligerent Ser Otho, was set to inherit <a href=\"/index.php/Stone_Hedge\" title=\"Stone Hedge\">Stone Hedge</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>It is unclear if he died by <a href=\"/index.php/212_AC\" title=\"212 AC\">212&#160;AC</a> or not. The conspirators of the <a href=\"/index.php/Second_Blackfyre_Rebellion\" title=\"Second Blackfyre Rebellion\">Second Blackfyre Rebellion</a> hoped for Otho to join the forces of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Bracken\" title=\"House Bracken\">House Bracken</a> to their own, which may imply Otho had succeeded his father.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Bracken_(father_of_Otho)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>His relation to <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Bracken_(Hand_of_the_King)\" title=\"Lord Bracken (Hand of the King)\">Lord Bracken</a> who was executed for treason in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_178_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">178&#160;AC</a> is unknown.\n</p>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:separate;font: 90% sans-serif;\">\n<tbody><tr align=\"center\"><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Bracken_(Hand_of_the_King)\" title=\"Lord Bracken (Hand of the King)\">Lord<br />Bracken</a></td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td c